47:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":["When the AI occasionally writes incorrect TypeScript code, ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"@autobe"}]," provides compilation error messages as feedback, allowing the AI to self-correct. This feedback process usually works correctly, so test code written by AI almost always compiles successfully. However, when using very small AI models, the ",["$","$L1b",null,{"href":"/api/types/_autobe_interface.IAutoBeTypeScriptCompileResult-1.html","prefetch":"$undefined","className":"x:focus-visible:nextra-focus x:text-primary-600 x:underline x:hover:no-underline x:decoration-from-font x:[text-underline-position:from-font]","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"IAutoBeTypeScriptCompileResult"}]}]," result might have ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"success := false"}],"."]}]
48:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":["The ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"step"}]," property indicates which requirements analysis report iteration the test code was written for.
